dct_description_sm: nuper correcta et in lucem edita per Fredericum De Wit.
3 bar scales on map, given in "Milliaria Hispanica Communia," "Milliaria Gallica Communia," and "Milliaria Germanica Communia."
North oriented toward right of sheet.
Latitudinal and longitudinal lines along margin.
Decorative cartouche (with cherubs), shield of Navarre, compass rose, ships.
Appears in de Wit's Atlas sive descriptio terrarum orbis, approximately 1688.
